resume /rɪˈzjuːm/

(resuming,resumed,resumes) 

1. V-T/V-I If you resume an activity or if it resumes , it begins again. 重新开始 [正式] 

例： After the war he resumed his duties at Wellesley College. 那场战争之后，他恢复了在韦尔斯利学院的任职。 

2. resumption N-UNCOUNT 重新开始 

例： It is premature to speculate about the resumption of negotiations. 考虑谈判的恢复还太早。 

3. V-T If you resume your seat or position, you return to the seat or position you were in before you moved. 重返 [正式] 

例： 'I changed my mind,' Blanche said, resuming her seat. “我改主意了，”布兰奇说，返回到她的座位上。

